cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.CG 

This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of binary search trees (BSTs) and their efficiency in various scenarios. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of search sequences, which falls under the sub-category cs.AL (Computational Complexity). The paper also introduces new properties and tools for analyzing BSTs, which could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
